<h1 id="ability-title" class="text-left ml-5">Your Game, My Rules</h1>
<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5">At 6th level, whenever you cast a spell that deals Fire or Cold damage you
  may spend 1 Sorcery point, this has the following effects depending on the subjects resistance or immunity to Fire or
  Cold damage.</p>

<ul class="text-left mx-5 mb-5">
  <li>
    <p id="ability-text">If the target has Immunity to Fire or Cold damage, they are treated as having Resistance to
      Fire or Cold damage.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p id="ability-text">If the target has Resistance to Fire or Cold damage, this Resistance is ignored.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    If the target has no Immunity or Resistance to Fire or Cold damage they take additional Fire or Cold damage equal to
    your Charisma modifier.
  </li>
</ul>

